        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 8:57PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 857 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mount Carmel, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Knox
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
